    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Crown-sized silver coins struck in the 16th through the 18th centuries. The term is extended to the "silver rider" coins struck as currency in the United Netherlands from 1659.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
